President Cyril Ramaphosa will have to hit all the right notes with South Africans later this week- if the state of the nation address is to get the thumbs up. CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to deliver the State of the Nation Address (Sona) on Thursday. Ramaphosa will have to inspire confidence in South Africans. He is expected to address the high unemployment rate, the country's contracting economy and troubled State-Owned Entreprises among other issues. Parliament says this years Sona is expected to be just under R2-million. The Sona will include guests such as former presidentsÂ Thabo Mbeki, FW de Klerk, Kgalema Motlanthe and former National Assembly Speaker Frene Ginwala.